<TITLE> Geeta Pasi meets with Ershad, other JP leaders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 18 (bdnews24.com) -- US charge d'affaires Geeta Pasi met with Jatiya Party chairman HM Ershad and other JP leaders Tuesday as part of her round of talks with political parties, a US embassy statement said. Pasi discussed the current political situation in Bangladesh and the status of the election roadmap with the party's leaders. The US envoy reiterated the US government's desire to see free, fair and fully participatory elections by the end of 2008 as promised by the caretaker government, the statement said. During the meeting, Pasi underscored the importance of the role political parties have to play in the process. She also stressed the importance of dialogue between the political parties and the government in order to establish the proper conditions for the elections. US embassy officials meet regularly with political party leaders and members of civil society as well as the government to discuss current issues in Bangladesh. Pasi is slated to meet leaders of BNP among other parties in the near future. bd
